          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Pb, Cu and Al-targets located behind the",
                "fragment recoil separator.  The ions U-238 were",
                "particly stripped by a thin copper foil thickness 205",
                "mg/cm**2 placed at the target position of the fragment",
                "separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two four stage multiple sampling ionization",
                "chambers, located before and after the target-",
                " MUSIC1 and  MUSIC2 were used to identify the nuclear",
                "charge.  With  MUSIC1 the primary U-ions were counted.",
                "The MUSIC2 was used either in a standard mode in order",
                "to measure the attenuation of the primary beam or to",
                "enumerate fission in events from the detection of a",
                "pair of ionizing fragments."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two large plastic scintillation detectors",
                "located behind the chamber and divided by a narrow",
                "horizontal slit in order to let the beam through."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCH"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy-ion synchrotron."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "FRS"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Fragment separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission fragments are emitted back-to-back",
                "isotropically in the projectile frame. The transfer of",
                "momentum between the target nucleus and the uranium",
                "projectile can be neglected and the fission kinematics",
                "is assumed to be same as far an in-flight decay taking",
                "place in the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By authors.  Fission events were sorted by different",
                "methods-",
                "counting the events for which two fragments of",
                "intermediate z were detected in music2.",
                "Measuring the energy loss of the two fragments.",
                "The spectrum of the energy loss for the first fragment",
                "of a pair was analyzed.",
                "Target-out contributions were subtracted with the three",
                "methods. It reduces the accuracy of the measurement.",
                "Together with the uncertainty due to the estimated of",
                "unresolved pairs of fragments,the precision ranges from",
                " 7% to 10% according to the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
